& [ReadinessVectorResult] is the measured readiness surface
  + [primitive_stability] is high because attention, boundary, outside, source authority, focal state, runtime registry, and manager state persist across commits
  + [schema_regularization] is medium_high because SOP contracts share subject, description, source, fields, must rules, outside, and graph-edge patterns
  + [corpus_quality] is high because source documents, manifests, canonical contracts, reviews, periphery records, and operating ticks are preserved
  + [evaluation_surface] is medium because runtime tests exist and LM Studio dry-run evidence exists, but compact manager task-family evaluation is incomplete
  + [compression_gain] is high because the active root has 96 import fields and 90 must rules while the manager lane needs only a small subset
  + [relationship_spectrum_stability] is medium because RelationshipEigenspectrum is defined but not yet populated by repeated index records
  + [authority_integrity] is high because SourceAuthorityRoot, CurrentFocalPoint, runtime registry, commit records, and GitHub push reports remain distinct
  + [runtime_boundary_clarity] is medium_high because read-only, proposal-only, mutation, worker launch, and training are named, but direct runner implementation remains pending

& [BurdenVectorResult] is the measured burden surface
  + [active_contract_count] is high because root Attention.sop imports 96 fields
  + [field_density] is high because the immediate root holds 90 must rules
  + [duplicate_role_pressure] is medium because compiler, kernel, scaffold, threshold, manager, and job-node surfaces overlap productively but need selection
  + [activation_noise] is medium because many layers can activate by relevance, but only a subset affects the LM Studio manager runner
  + [context_load] is high because loading the full active root is too large for lightweight local manager work
  + [stale_remnant_pressure] is medium because older F:\.sop and prior AttentionFramework remnants remain reference material, now bounded by LegacyContractReinforcementPolicy
  + [validation_drag] is medium because SOP-only changes validate quickly, but runtime manager work will need stronger schema tests

& [CompactManagerKernelRecommendation] is the next safe work packet
  + [kernel_purpose] is give LM Studio a small manager-readable SOP packet without the full active root burden
  + [minimum_contract_set] is LocalAIManagerPrimary, CodexLMStudioOrchestrationWorkspace, WorkspaceState, Queue, Runbook, WorkerPacketTemplate, SOPLanguagePrimerForLocalAgents, SOPWorkerBootPacket, SecurityHonestyGovernance, FrameReferenceIntegrity, CurrentFocalPoint, and TaskFrameLaunchQueue
  + [excluded_from_minimum] is photonic contracts, social swarm fabric, concept refinement fabric, transformer readiness, relationship eigenspectrum, hyperbolic navigation, and broad historical completed-task list unless specifically requested by a manager task
  + [output_shape] is compact_manager_kernel_bundle with role, task queue, allowed actions, blocked actions, handoff threshold, schema, stop policy, and capture target
  + [validation_need] is compare local manager output against schema, outside preservation, task routing, and authority boundary
  + [next_after_kernel] is implement or refine Task_161 direct LM Studio endpoint manager runner using the compact bundle

